<br>
School had just gotten out at the high school, and of course there are people who walk home. Others drive, get a ride, whatever.<br>
<br>
So, people are walking across the street. Usually in huge groups. The signals for pedestrians are weird, IMO. They say &quot;WALK&quot; or show the walking guy for like 2 seconds, then have the blinking &quot;DON'T WALK&quot; or red hand for about 2 more seconds, then the blinking stops and it just says &quot;DON'T WALK&quot; or has the red hand.<br>
<br>
