<br>
And yes, the law enforcement in my area is notorious for only enforcing law for quotas. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 4:03:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4731.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Nope, dont have stats to back that up. Just the multitude of individuals I have met. All ages, all demographics. Why isnt it legal? Because it has never been put to vote. Trolo, I dont know what state you live in, but DUI refers to alcohol, not drugs. To the people that think DUP(driving under pot) is the same as DWI, you need to get a reality check, or go get high.<br>
